    "overall_conclusion": "EXPERIMENT J CONCLUSION: Within-species grammar is partially conserved: human datasets share substantially more motif pairs than cross-species comparisons. Helical phasing is a universal grammar property conserved across all species. GSI-expression coupling shows moderate variation across human datasets. Grammar conservation at the motif-pair level shows partial evidence, with some properties conserved and others divergent. This supports a model where (1) the repertoire of grammar-capable motif pairs is partially shared within species, (2) helical phasing is a universal biophysical constraint, but (3) specific grammar rules may be enhancer-context dependent rather than purely species-dependent."
